'''Iain MacDonald''' is an Irish entrepreneur.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.independent.ie/business/iain-macdonald-2280510.html | work=Irish Independent | title=Iain MacDonald | date=30 November 2012}}</ref> He founded Perlico in 2003, an Irish consumer telecommunications company, and later sold it to [[Vodafone Ireland]] in a 2007 deal reportedly worth €80 million contingent on subsequent earnings.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doubts raised on Perlico worth |url=http://www.techcentral.ie/article.aspx?id=11544 |work=TechCentral.ie |publisher=[[ComputerScope]] |date=November 26, 2007 |accessdate=2012-12-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406171015/http://www.techcentral.ie/article.aspx?id=11544 |archivedate=April 6, 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Perlico Communications has announced its intention to enter the Irish mobile market |url = http://www.rte.ie/news/2005/0511/perlico-business.html |work = [[RTÉ.ie]] |date = January 26, 2007 |accessdate = 2012-12-17}}</ref> In its final year of independent operations, Perlico reported a loss of €7 million on revenues of €40 million.<ref>{{cite news|last=Errity |first=Stephen |title=Vodafone acquires Perlico for EUR80m |url=http://www.enn.ie/article/10123425.html |accessdate=18 December 2012 |newspaper=ElectricNews.Net Ltd. |date=13 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130213142553/http://www.enn.ie/article/10123425.html |archivedate=13 February 2013 |df= }}</ref>
In 2009, MacDonald founded "Weeedle", later renamed [[SkillPages]], a skills-based social network.<ref>{{cite news|last=Arthur|first=Charles|title=Irish tech startups: Weedle won't wobble from cataloguing skills|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/blog/2010/nov/24/irish-startups-weedle-skills-ambition|accessdate=18 December 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=24 November 2010|location=London}}</ref>
