'''''Næringslivsavisen NA24.no AS''''' or ''NA24'' is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[online newspaper|online]] [[business]] [[newspaper]]. It was created on 22 March 2006 as a merger between the business sections of ''[[Nettavisen]]'', ''[[Fædrelandsvennen]]'', ''[[Stavanger Aftenblad]]'', ''[[Bergens Tidende]]'' and ''[[Adresseavisen]]'', and the online newspapers ''iMarkedet'' and ''Propaganda''. It has 400,000 weekly users, and [[editor-in-chief]] is Inge Berge. It is owned 40% by the [[TV2 (Norway)|TV2 Group]], 20% by Aller Internett and 10% by each the four participating regional newspapers.
