{{Italic title}} 
'''The Invisible Edge''' is a 2009 business book written by authors Mark Blaxill and Ralph Eckardt that focuses on the unappreciated value of [[intellectual property]] and how it can be harnessed by firms to create sustainable advantages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipwatchdog.com/2009/06/05/book-review-the-invisible-edge/id=3937/|title=Book Review: The Invisible Edge- Patents & Patent Law|date=5 June 2009|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.automationworld.com/industrial-internet-things/invisible-edge-internet-things|title=The Invisible Edge of the Internet of Things - Automation World|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/intellectual-property-pioneer-peter-detkin-joins-sherpa-technology-group-formerly-3lp-advisors-300387500.html|title=Intellectual Property Pioneer Peter Detkin Joins Sherpa Technology Group, formerly 3LP Advisors|first=Sherpa Technology|last=Group|publisher=}}</ref>

